* Types of Databases
** SQL or Relational Databases
*** Data stored in tables with predefined schema
*** **ACID properties (Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability)**
*** Examples: MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle DB
** NoSQL Databases
*** Non-tabular data storage, flexible schema
*** Different types: document, key-value, column-family, graph
*** **BASE properties (Basically Available, Soft state, Eventually consistent)**
*** Examples: MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis
** Object-Oriented Databases (OODBMS)
*** Objects stored in database with their attributes and methods
*** Supports inheritance, encapsulation and polymorphism
*** Examples: db4o, ObjectStore, Versant
